### Cyber Security (Basics)

Cybersecurity means keeping computers, networks, and data safe from hackers and attacks.

It helps protect important information, such as passwords, personal data, and files, from theft or damage.

## Basic Ideas
Confidentiality – Only the right people can see the data
Integrity – Others should not change data
Availability – Data should be available when needed

## Common Threats
Malware – Harmful software like viruses
Phishing – Fake messages to trick people
Hacking – Unauthorized access to systems

## Basic Tools & Concepts
Firewall – Protects systems from unwanted access
Encryption – Keeps data safe by converting it into secret form
Vulnerability – A weakness in a system
Penetration Testing – Testing systems to find security problems

## Why It Is Important
Keeps personal data safe
Protects systems from attacks
Helps maintain privacy
